metadata.description: Stores the first name of an individual. The values in this column are of string data type and provide a way to uniquely identify each person.
Middle name of an individual. It stores the middle name of each person. The values in this column are of string data type and provide additional information about the person's name.
Stores the last name of an individual. The values in this column are of string data type and provide a way to identify the family name of each person in the dataset.
Unique identifier for each record in the dataset. It stores numerical values in long data type, providing a way to uniquely identify each record in the dataset.
Represents the salary of an individual. It stores numerical values in integer data type, indicating the monetary compensation received by each individual for their work.

Indicates whether the data entry has been processed or not. It stores boolean values, where 'true' indicates that the data entry has been processed and 'false' indicates that it has not been processed yet.
Represents the date of birth of an individual. It stores values in the date data type, indicating the birth date of each person.

Stores the weight of an individual. It stores numerical values in double data type, indicating the weight of each individual in the dataset. The values in this column provide information about the physical characteristics of each individual.

Represents the state in which an individual resides. It stores the name of the state as a string value. This column provides information about the geographical location of each individual in the dataset.
Represents the city where an individual resides. It stores the name of the city as a string value. This column provides information about the geographical location of each individual in the dataset.

Indicates the gender of an individual. It stores the gender of each person as a string value, representing whether they are male or female. This column provides information about the gender distribution in the dataset.
